 summary. There might be a risk with the YAML/JSON examples requiring optional modules, so we should avoid those formats unless necessary. Also, it's important that environment variable behavior changed in version 3.0.0, and I should recommend using the constructor map for environment sources instead. If the user asks for guidance on environment variables and system properties in the agent guidance, we should clarify how to set up the tests properly.\n\n**Clarifying agent guidance**\n\nIâ€™m thinking about the agent guidance being non-deterministic. It seems I could specify that the setup can involve environment or system properties in agent guidance. If Iâ€™m adding guidance about requiring system properties for tests, maybe I should classify it as advisory preparation instead of mandatory. To avoid ambiguity, I might want to say that no additional environment variables or system properties are required. Iâ€™ll also need to ensure any risks regarding optional parsers are clearly covered, and valid JSON is essential.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_033258bc2391da0f016a40a3a372ec819394f4cbf279d0a924\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqQKOxkrHXqtgGn0IZea_lsK7Ag5Qp6FUF8YYQpdpnmzIKBp0qMODnyTDZD2EuR2lgVYvw98QpOvf5Mz3gp5BIIjIEwHfWwAu9xs0AQwHIPppw-OqsO1j4n870gh9zCGXggjjsGG41GCDbm3lzUfj4TTfnwJ1gGxw7fJqYGbHPMXhFT7ip_3wJgq7_zhRFrF8Xbf39QRcR1KiaqTD5Bcu2lG-Gkz2I1tCp28WsVEiLNGQqKjPCSMOO5SLMkrmLwJZjXWL_lRZGF6PcYs9kNBxtSYsO0Lcjr3UqkEhCO83hVQLtTtQ10sml8kyyPvXkmahyohrdErSq9BXWhBX-F6P4FWTPAHe8W-fVwE8i9Uq1J-Qaxj4uWt4-MXFpKkwrvOkgnRFgpqaWS-oXAe16kci47leYo8X5qp3psbGXjC0EvvwTQsRqAOWVUSzDTQ0TMbyE_AtA8Vmtmtl1z2JLFsC8oDonagS5jm4iSOs3aXQ947k1-Xe3CP3eSQUMEw3Fj-9xo6afWGunn1V2Q4Z9QnqMycSzaBkq9hTztyWNkwIEMp3vTs4E8PiQ_bPxu_-kzB-6wXzJo5JbRXxYl4ZZ-specK3e614Fd1e7bw6l_q4BhbwerzwrAMaCu2D0RN8kHvAdSutlXelBCzhuTTjS_aQTTmh0y5Q9Edos1ARLcT8tbt5Lshb4bVQXLfGLivHUWW1xZYiF4rfSXezRMGZ8DFhveFTqqUaR_--H1g6v0gOe8xFvCHydOqjbNBsFLQ6HUMEcHukyh_n549UKR_IM3eiTxm15f9cTyGF7IAyNf3e